    "body": "Note: This PR builds on top of #37408 as it relates to the same issue: #37405. I separated the commits & PRs because I thought it would be easier to review & I wasn't sure both changes in behavior were necessarily desired. Modifying startup behavior could break existing configs: even if these changes are in line with the documented behavior.\r\n\r\nI'm marking this PR as a draft for now until #37408 is merged so the diff becomes easier to review. (Since this PR contains both commits: to prevent merge conflicts.)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Problem:\r\n\r\n`$NVIM_APPNAME` was not respected when searching `$XDG_CONFIG_DIRS` for config files during startup. Instead, it hardcoded \"nvim\" when constructing paths like `$XDG_CONFIG_DIRS/nvim/init.{vim,lua}`, ignoring the `$NVIM_APPNAME` environment variable.\r\n\r\nThis meant that config files like `$XDG_CONFIG_DIRS/myapp/init.lua` were not loaded, even though `$NVIM_APPNAME` was set to \"myapp\".\r\n\r\n### Solution:\r\n\r\nUse `get_appname()` instead of hardcoded \"nvim\" for `$XDG_CONFIG_DIRS` paths in `do_system_initialization()` and `do_user_initialization()`. This makes `$XDG_CONFIG_DIRS` behave consistently with `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME`, which already respected `$NVIM_APPNAME`.\r\n\r\nAs documented in `runtime/doc/starting.txt` (L1440-L1441):\r\n> \"In the help wherever `$XDG_CONFIG_…/nvim` is mentioned it is understood as `$XDG_CONFIG_…/$NVIM_APPNAME`.\"\r\n\r\nSee:\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/43339dee40aa7731cc644315c15080e30aa1a67c/runtime/doc/starting.txt#L1440-L1441\r\n\r\nRelates to https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/37405\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nSince I don't have any experience in the neovim codebase I had my friendly AI help with the implementation. Here's the session: https://opncd.ai/share/Lg2x1H1g. This session is a continuation of the session used in #37408: about halfway through I state \"Everything related to loading `init.lua` is commited and in a PR. Let's see if we can also tackle taking NVIM_APPNAME into account.\"\r\n\r\nI reviewed the code to the best of my ability and it seems pretty OK. Feedback or improvements are very welcome!\r\n\r\nI also built and ran locally, the `example-xdg-dir/example-nvim-appname/init.lua` file is now sourced as expected. (See reproduction steps in #37405.)\r\n\r\nStartup log:\r\n\r\n```\r\n...\r\ncould not source \"$VIM/sysinit.vim\"\r\ncould not source \"/Users/jessevanderpluijm/.config/example-nvim-appname/init.vim\"\r\nsourcing \"/Users/jessevanderpluijm/Code/forks/neovim/example-xdg-config-dir/example-nvim-appname/init.lua\"\r\n                                                                                                          hello from XDG_CONFIG_DIRS/example-nvim-appname/init.lua\r\nfinished sourcing /Users/jessevanderpluijm/Code/forks/neovim/example-xdg-config-dir/example-nvim-appname/init.lua\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\n<!--\r\n  Thank you for contributing to Neovim!\r\n  If this is your first time, check out https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#pull-requests-prs\r\n  for our PR guidelines.\r\n-->\r\n",
